abstract = {Key Points: 7 • Urbanization effect as big as GHG warming for the near future for minimum tem-8 perature 9 • Doubling of the minimum temperature change due to urbanization 10 • Afforestation has positive impact on reducing temperature increase Abstract 12 Changes in the land surface interact with a changing climate. Moreover, the impact of 13 land surface changes on the local and regional climate can be as large as the impact of 14 increasing greenhouse gas emissions. The land surface-climate interactions are best rep-15 resented by high-resolution models to capture the mesoscale circulation features. The fu-16 ture land surface changes are preferably represented by scenarios that illustrate plausible 17 storylines. Furthermore, the impact of future urbanization is relevant for the highly ur-18 banized region of Europe. In this study, we assess the interactions between climate and 19 land surface dynamics by modeling the near future climate state for Western Europe based 20 on a policy-driven land use change scenario at high resolution. The global climate model 21 CNRM-CM5.1 has been downscaled to the regional climate of Western Europe by using 22 ALARO-SURFEX at 4 km horizontal resolution. SURFEX provides a parameterization of 23 the urban physical properties so that the impact of urban surfaces on the regional climate 24 can be modeled realistically. Results are interpreted with respect to the near future cli-25 mate change without land surface changes. The near future presents a uniform temperature 26 increase of 0.3-0.6 • C. This is in contrast to changes by the land surface that are more 27 heterogeneous in space and much stronger at the local scale. Deforestation and conversion 28 to arable land diminishes climate change effects, whereas urbanization results in an en-29 hancing effect of climate change. Moreover, urbanization is as big as the radiative forcing 30 warming for minimum temperature.},
